  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed and a screening sensitivity study was conducted informally across turbulence model parameters and inlet boundary conditions — results indicated moderate sensitivity to near-wall treatment. All credibility factor gaps remain. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Accepted pending sponsor acknowledgment of residual risk.",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou2-hemolysis-absolute",
